                <h3 class="text-center">Why Home School?</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>My child has special needs that we can meet better working one on one.</li>
                    <li>My child was being bullied in public school.</li>
                    <li>
                        My child wanted to move faster than the rest of the class, he can do that at home. At home he can move at his own speed.
                    </li>
                    <li>We can learn in a way that works for me and my kiddos.</li>
                    <li>
                        I know my child’s strengths and weakness and can teach them with these in mind, unlike a teacher with 25-35 students in their room.
                    </li>
                    <li>We can make play, which is the learning language of children, the basis for our children’s learning.</li>
                    <li>We can travel, see the world, take our kids on our business trips, anything we are doing, we just fit school into and around it.</li>
                    <li>
                        Our child has special health issues that can be better accommodated at home.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Our children gets to learn in a more real world setting than a classroom.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        I want my children to learn in a way that is based on our faith beliefs.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        We can base learning around our child’s interests and passions.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        We can teach our children in a way that helps them become entrepreneurs.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Our children can be involved in extracurricular activities they enjoy that would not be possible if they had a public-school schedule.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Our son can have a part -time day job in a field he is interested in during part of the day when he is homeschooled.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Our child’s diagnosis requires a special diet, and they were getting contaminated at school and getting sick.
                    </li>
                </ul>
